<subSubSection id="8B9961D4F37519E66AE9A929288F89FA" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6F1D2A1C35472D53C968DDE5D7180E9E" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="056BF59E9BDAF79A249F2BD20735A815" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
<taxonomicName id="454B5A5BA93D10309DC6C30143AC688C" authorityName="J. F. Liu, S. R. Lan &amp; Y. C. Liang" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum pingnanense" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pingnanense">
<emphasis id="3DD5FE9BF22FDF613D0E3FF18A3DCC8D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Bulbophyllum pingnanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="225AC5DB486CAF6A0973C276A24A2AA2" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipedunculatum">
<emphasis id="9FAF88BF131A43FC01BCCBB0B7F60736" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
T.C. Hsu &amp; S.W. Chung and 
<taxonomicName id="3AD38F318DE9BE3589ACBF2ED11BAF24" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum albociliatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albociliatum">
<emphasis id="E1F8D1CAC22A45C9FABD10A49D4BD418" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Bulbophyllum albociliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(T.S. Liu &amp; H.Y. Su) K. Nackejima. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1BFDADB707C064BDB338D67520E319C4" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevipedunculatum">
<emphasis id="07349D27A5679A52FC85E1E214ADDDDA" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a longer dorsal sepal with either an obtuse or an acute apex and longer white ciliate on margins; longer and lanceolate lateral sepals; and glabrous lip. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D248CD499D667CD94AF709E430D2CAB8" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum albociliatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albociliatum">
<emphasis id="067CF68C1855FBCABC47116B1D0A1D42" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Bulbophyllum albociliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its shorter inflorescence, a longer dorsal sepal with either an obtuse or an acute apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="523577BF5EFAACE6CFC90895FAF380AD" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" type="description">
<paragraph id="D445C35160F6F71FADFBBB1051F0BB76" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0930AA9260E4B0E6CFD120B8BCA8D242" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
Epiphytic herb. Rhizome creeping, slender, 0.6-1 mm in diam. Pseudobulbs 0.6-2.5 cm apart on rhizome, obovate-elliptic, 0.5-1.7 cm, 3-6 mm in diam., with a terminal leaf. Leaf sessile; blade oblong to linear-oblong, 1.8-6.6 
<normalizedToken id="0A9A4DAB4AAFA8A1C53865D4096E401E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6-1.2 cm, apex obtuse to retuse. Scape arising from base of pseudobulb, ca. 1.1 cm, umbel 3-5 flowered; peduncle slender, ca. 0.6 mm in diam., with 3 or 4 sheaths; floral bracts triangular, 2-3 mm. Pedicel and ovary ca. 4 mm. Flowers orange red. Dorsal sepal concave, ovate, abaxially papillose, ca. 5 
<normalizedToken id="3EA3536F85CBFD3E5E84E60F88F1E2C4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, margins long white ciliate, apex obtuse or acute; lateral sepals lanceolate, abaxially papillose, 10-12 
<normalizedToken id="8822F9790E1F874D727480141311605C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 2 mm, slightly twisted near the base, with their upper and lower edges often loosely adhering, margins glabrous, apex acute. Petals ovate, 2.7-3.0 
<normalizedToken id="291AD564EBF1E44B5180D9B4676640A1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-2.0 mm, margins long white ciliate, apex rounded. Lip recurved, ovate-triangular, ca. 3 mm, abaxially deeply grooved, base attached to end of column foot by a mobile joint. Column yellow, subterete, ca. 1-2 mm, with a distinct foot, ca. 1.0-2.5 mm, conspicuously winged; stelidia triangular, slender; anther cap subglobose; pollinia 4, in 2 pairs, without appendages.
</paragraph>
