<paragraph id="2AC311075C43AE1D3BAAE26B5E713488" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="AEE68ED10BFD5E8585C0CF4CE6D9A977" authorityName="J. F. Liu, S. R. Lan &amp; Y. C. Liang" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bulbophyllum pingnanense" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pingnanense">
<emphasis id="CEB8A7DD5204B19EDC7F697135E4F269" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Bulbophyllum pingnanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so far only known within Pingnan, Fujian, China (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B3691B544356594CD1DF22AB5140002B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Bulbophyllum pingnanense, Bulbophyllum brevipedunculatum and Bulbophyllum albociliatum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.65.8254.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/94170" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">3</figureCitation>
). It is epiphytic on steep rock in the edge of evergreen coniferous and broad-leaved mixed forest, which is mainly composed of 
<taxonomicName id="2452A45E0C5BFDC8EDAAB465B85040D6" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanopsis eyrei" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="eyrei">
<emphasis id="82C79E0AF6D8D64DD4B6D2B80916BA6B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Castanopsis eyrei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Champ. ex Benth.) Hutch. (
<taxonomicName id="569314EA75F80AB57B2D443558A42E1D" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="76B11BCE4E5D4786889ECEF0CAD11CBF" class="Pinopsida" family="Taxodiaceae" genus="Cunninghamia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cunninghamia lanceolata" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis id="BDE11C0C07F3E80A5DB2B4222ABFDC7D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Cunninghamia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lamb.) Hook. (
<taxonomicName id="7849B58C277A78E5B56F494C5E7ED3A6" class="Pinopsida" family="Taxodiaceae" genus="Cunninghamia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="family">Taxodiaceae</taxonomicName>
). Other orchids, 
<taxonomicName id="797364DFE9109D42F6C85DB492795F48" authorityName="Schltr" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Blume" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Amitostigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Amitostigma gracile" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="E2248533749585C032A0E6FFD31C3651" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Amitostigma gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bl.) Schltr., 
<taxonomicName id="3552AB0C3CAC85472E54CAF6E143775A" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pholidota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pholidota cantonensis" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cantonensis">
<emphasis id="BC15AC33A64C26A196F970442EE138DE" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Pholidota cantonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rolfe, 
<taxonomicName id="822311BBD0EF895ECA592308E3D3B690" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Cymbidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbidium floribundum" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="floribundum">
<emphasis id="A5AE079D24C5964F97338E6129F07F2E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Cymbidium floribundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lindl. and 
<taxonomicName id="B8E5AE929F40F5A9B84C871DDE7FAADA" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleione" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleione formosana" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis id="8B7354546E5B5D8DDEC9A09CDC31E5E6" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Pleione formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hayata, were found growing nearby this new species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="AA1D99527A9395B116EAEAE1A184677B" ID-Zenodo-Dep="979907" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.65.8254.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/94170" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="2C3FCF000B718466D6829B3079E77B79" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
